SIMPLE: suffragette
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suffragette
<hw>Suf`fra*gette"</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A woman who advocates the
right to vote for women; a woman suffragist.</def> <note>This term was
applied mostly to women in the United States prior to the adoption of
the 19th amendment to the constitution in 1920, giving women the right
to vote. Modern use of this term usually refers to the women who
advocated female suffrage{5} in the years prior to 1920.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffraginous</ent>⟦br⟧
